recordings.rmk:
Apparent vocal mimicry of Carolina Wren in this cut. Possibly same individual recorded mimicking an Eastern Phoebe in soft song (cf XC307484). Bird was perched near the top of an oak tree overlooking lawns approximately 10 meters from me. Wren-like phrases were persistent off and on for several minutes. Heard initially as I approached the grounds and then continued as I located the bird. Note the terminal phrases typical of AMRO songs occurring on the end of the wren-like phrases early in the recording with a gradual transition to fairly normal AMRO song. Full recording from which this is cut is ~ 3 minutes. 

Recorded on an iPhone 6 using the Voice Memo app. High-pass filtered at 800 Hz and then amplified 6dB.

29-acre estate centrally located in Oxford, MS consisting of antebellum home surrounded by lawns and adjacent forest. Privet hedges and small thickets divide the grounds into distinct lawn units. A path from the end of the parking area leads northward ~1 km through the forest to the northern edge of the property abutting the University of Mississippi campus
